"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(DISTINCT d.driverId) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT d2.driverId)) AS percentage\nFROM \n    drivers d\nJOIN \n    lapTimes lt ON d.driverId = lt.driverId\nJOIN \n    results r ON lt.raceId = r.raceId AND d.driverId = r.driverId\nWHERE \n    d.dob < '1985-01-01' \n    AND lt.lap > 50 \n    AND r.raceId IN (\n        SELECT raceId \n        FROM races \n        WHERE year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2005\n    );\n``` \n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of drivers who were born before 1985 and completed more than 50 laps in races held between 2000 and 2005. It uses joins to connect the relevant tables and applies the necessary filters in the WHERE clause."